1
00:00:01,133 --> 00:00:02,567
<i>Tell me the last thing
your father said to you.</i>

2
00:00:02,733 --> 00:00:04,100
<i> Why would I ever tell you?</i>

3
00:00:04,267 --> 00:00:05,400
- [KICK LANDS]
- [CRIES OUT IN PAIN]

4
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:08,067
<i>If you still want to
be able to breathe, you'll talk.</i>

5
00:00:08,233 --> 00:00:10,567
<i>- It's about Uncle Andy.
- What about Uncle Andy?</i>

6
00:00:10,667 --> 00:00:13,300
<i>I'm not sure I still want him
as a partner for the hotel.</i>

7
00:00:13,433 --> 00:00:16,233
<i>It's him, right?
He's the man who took Juan?</i>

8
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:18,767
<i>If he has an accomplice
on the inside,</i>

9
00:00:18,933 --> 00:00:21,367
<i>we can't report this.
The three of us are in danger.</i>

10
00:00:21,467 --> 00:00:24,033
<i> Really, Uncle?
</i>You're finally going to invest?

11
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:26,567
<i> Ah, yes. Oh,
</i>and don't forget to bring Sari.

12
00:00:26,733 --> 00:00:28,533
<i> Sari, let's talk.</i>

13
00:00:29,733 --> 00:00:31,233
<i> What are you doing here?</i>

14
00:00:41,300 --> 00:00:43,433
The guest was just inquiring,
sir.

15
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:44,633
We're fully booked.

16
00:00:46,433 --> 00:00:47,600
Really?

17
00:00:47,767 --> 00:00:50,100
- But he said there was--
- No vacancies anymore.

18
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:52,933
- Hm? Sir Gio...
- I said there's no room left.

19
00:00:53,100 --> 00:00:57,267
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

20
00:00:57,367 --> 00:00:59,900
I'm not even going
to charge you for that coffee.

21
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,733
Just go to another hotel.

22
00:01:03,767 --> 00:01:05,100
[SCOFFS]

23
00:01:05,267 --> 00:01:07,100
Do you even know who I am?

24
00:01:09,533 --> 00:01:12,500
[GIO] According to the card...
you're Peter Montevilla.

25
00:01:13,633 --> 00:01:16,600
Now you can leave.
We're fully booked.

26
00:01:20,967 --> 00:01:24,100
Even if I don't get
a room here...

27
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:26,833
I can still stay
at the restaurant, right?

28
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:30,833
Besides...
I'm here to talk to Luna.

29
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,300
She's not here.

30
00:01:34,133 --> 00:01:35,133
Get out.

31
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:40,300
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

32
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:42,800
I heard good things
about this hotel.

33
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:48,467
But...

34
00:01:50,667 --> 00:01:52,667
I guess this is
how the staff acts here.

35
00:01:56,033 --> 00:01:59,667
Or maybe I should just
come back...

36
00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:03,633
when Luna is around.

37
00:02:06,167 --> 00:02:07,633
After all...

38
00:02:07,733 --> 00:02:09,967
she's the one
I really want to talk to.

39
00:02:10,067 --> 00:02:16,833
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

40
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:38,667
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

41
00:03:31,467 --> 00:03:34,933
[DOORKNOB RATTLING]

42
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:36,933
[DOOR CLICKS OPEN]

43
00:03:37,033 --> 00:03:41,767
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

44
00:03:41,933 --> 00:03:43,267
Close it.

45
00:03:45,100 --> 00:03:47,000
[DOOR CLOSES]

46
00:03:47,133 --> 00:03:53,900
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

47
00:03:56,067 --> 00:03:57,700
Does this belong
to Juan's father?

48
00:03:59,033 --> 00:04:00,467
Wait,
what are we even doing here?

49
00:04:00,633 --> 00:04:02,133
This is where
the kidnapping happened.

50
00:04:02,300 --> 00:04:05,867
Exactly.
This is where it happened.

51
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,933
This is where we start.

52
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:11,267
- What are we going to do?
- [GASPS]

53
00:04:11,367 --> 00:04:13,133
- Justin!
- You startled us!

54
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:14,833
Go slower next time!

55
00:04:18,133 --> 00:04:20,467
- Don't rush in like that!
- Don't just burst in like that!

56
00:04:21,667 --> 00:04:23,300
What's the plan?

57
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:26,167
We're going to trace
exactly what happened here,

58
00:04:26,333 --> 00:04:28,033
or see if Juan or his
father left anything behind

59
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:31,533
that could lead us
to where Juan is.

60
00:04:31,700 --> 00:04:35,667
Is that the goal?
To find out where Juan is?

61
00:04:35,767 --> 00:04:36,833
Yes.

62
00:04:36,933 --> 00:04:38,633
I need that information
to find the true connection

63
00:04:38,733 --> 00:04:40,667
between Leon
and Juan's father.

64
00:04:41,867 --> 00:04:43,233
Okay.

65
00:04:43,367 --> 00:04:45,500
- Let's lock up first.
- Huh?

66
00:04:45,667 --> 00:04:48,067
The person who took Juan
might come back.

67
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:49,333
Trixie...

68
00:04:49,500 --> 00:04:52,833
people like that are used
to forcing doors open.

69
00:04:52,933 --> 00:04:55,467
Locking it won't do anything.
We need to hurry.

70
00:04:55,567 --> 00:04:59,033
At least if it's locked,
we'll have time--

71
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:00,800
[JUSTIN]
Time for what?

72
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:04,633
T-Time... to leave.

73
00:05:06,367 --> 00:05:08,600
[LOCK RATTLING, CLICKS]

74
00:05:09,867 --> 00:05:11,867
Is everyone locked in?

75
00:05:13,233 --> 00:05:15,167
Let's go, hurry up.

76
00:05:15,267 --> 00:05:16,900
Let's go, let's start.

77
00:05:22,133 --> 00:05:23,533
[TRIXIE] Oh my god.

78
00:05:27,867 --> 00:05:30,700
[LINE RINGING]

79
00:05:30,867 --> 00:05:32,900
[PHONE BUZZING]

80
00:05:33,067 --> 00:05:36,900
What is it now? Just
when I'm trying to find a job.

81
00:05:37,100 --> 00:05:40,867
Universe,
please tell him to stop!

82
00:05:40,967 --> 00:05:46,133
[PLAYFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

83
00:05:46,267 --> 00:05:48,033
[GROANS LOUDLY]

84
00:05:48,133 --> 00:05:52,567
[PHONE BUZZING]

85
00:05:52,733 --> 00:05:54,767
Leave me alone,
Martin Madrigal!

86
00:05:54,933 --> 00:05:57,733
I told you, no matter
how much you pressure me,

87
00:05:57,900 --> 00:06:00,567
I'm not backing down.

88
00:06:00,733 --> 00:06:01,733
[SCOFFS]

89
00:06:03,100 --> 00:06:04,067
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

90
00:06:04,167 --> 00:06:05,267
[CALL DISCONNECTED TONE]

91
00:06:05,433 --> 00:06:07,567
She's ignoring my calls?

92
00:06:07,767 --> 00:06:10,100
Maybe her battery just died,
sir?

93
00:06:10,267 --> 00:06:12,433
Why do you keep
calling her anyway?

94
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:15,767
Well, why can't she at
least find out why I'm calling?

95
00:06:15,867 --> 00:06:18,767
I wouldn't call
if it weren't important.

96
00:06:18,933 --> 00:06:20,233
That's the thing, sir.

97
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:22,600
You're calling her about work,

98
00:06:22,767 --> 00:06:24,633
but didn't she already resign?

99
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:27,333
My reason is for
the hotel investment, Monette.

100
00:06:27,467 --> 00:06:29,800
She knows how important that is.

101
00:06:29,967 --> 00:06:31,833
It's because
you hurt her feelings, sir.

102
00:06:31,967 --> 00:06:34,967
Of course she's not going
to go easy on you right away.

103
00:06:35,133 --> 00:06:36,500
I was just telling her off

104
00:06:36,633 --> 00:06:38,600
so she'd stop talking
to that guest.

105
00:06:38,767 --> 00:06:41,933
If I let them be, who knows?
He'd take advantage of her!

106
00:06:42,067 --> 00:06:45,267
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

107
00:06:45,367 --> 00:06:49,633
Mm! So that's why!

108
00:06:49,733 --> 00:06:51,467
What do you mean "that's why"?

109
00:06:51,633 --> 00:06:53,467
You're concerned about Sari,

110
00:06:53,567 --> 00:06:55,633
that's why you said
those things.

111
00:06:57,733 --> 00:06:59,700
Well, maybe. I don't know.

112
00:06:59,833 --> 00:07:02,367
Regardless,
she needs to answer my call.

113
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:04,967
You know what's better, sir?

114
00:07:05,133 --> 00:07:08,200
Go to her. Explain yourself.

115
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:15,333
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

116
00:07:16,700 --> 00:07:19,000
[TRIXIE] Wait,
what are we even looking for?

117
00:07:20,767 --> 00:07:23,500
Any clue that points to Juan.

118
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:26,733
Maybe those men who
took him left something behind.

119
00:07:26,867 --> 00:07:28,167
Okay.

120
00:07:28,333 --> 00:07:31,867
The house is a mess. Are
we even going to find anything?

121
00:07:32,033 --> 00:07:34,967
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

122
00:07:35,067 --> 00:07:37,700
Cheska. Cheska.

123
00:07:37,867 --> 00:07:40,033
You know you can't use that,
right?

124
00:07:41,233 --> 00:07:42,533
Why not?

125
00:07:43,533 --> 00:07:45,067
What if we actually find
something here?

126
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:49,367
Besides, no one's around.
This is great for the podcast.

127
00:07:51,133 --> 00:07:55,933
Cheska, we're still trespassing.
What if Juan sues you?

128
00:07:56,067 --> 00:07:57,167
Huh?

129
00:07:57,267 --> 00:08:00,367
Why would he sue me?
We're doing this to find him,

130
00:08:00,467 --> 00:08:02,733
and he's going to sue me?
That's rich.

131
00:08:02,900 --> 00:08:05,900
Cheska,
please don't be difficult.

132
00:08:07,067 --> 00:08:09,367
Okay, friend!

133
00:08:09,467 --> 00:08:13,167
But what if we actually
find something, right?

134
00:08:13,267 --> 00:08:15,867
Cheska, be serious.

135
00:08:15,967 --> 00:08:18,167
Stop thinking
about your podcast.

136
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:20,667
[CLICKS TONGUE]

137
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:27,733
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

138
00:08:33,267 --> 00:08:34,967
Is this a map of Hotel 88?

139
00:08:36,467 --> 00:08:38,567
Why... Why does Juan have this?

140
00:08:38,733 --> 00:08:41,800
[MUSIC BECOMES TENSE]

141
00:08:41,933 --> 00:08:44,933
Or Juan's father?
This is his house, right?

142
00:08:46,233 --> 00:08:49,933
But isn't it even weirder?

143
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:53,267
Why would Juan's father
have a map of Hotel 88?

144
00:08:53,433 --> 00:08:55,933
I thought they said
it was missing.

145
00:08:56,133 --> 00:08:58,000
He was a contractor
for Hotel 88 before.

146
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:01,833
He was hired for the renovation.

147
00:09:01,967 --> 00:09:02,900
Mm. Okay.

148
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,933
It makes sense
why he has a map.

149
00:09:06,533 --> 00:09:07,900
But what's this?

150
00:09:09,467 --> 00:09:10,900
Look at that.

151
00:09:12,467 --> 00:09:14,067
Yeah, you're right.

152
00:09:14,167 --> 00:09:16,067
What is it?

153
00:09:16,167 --> 00:09:17,800
- [LOUD CRASH IN THE DISTANCE]
- [GASPS]

154
00:09:17,967 --> 00:09:20,100
- Hey! Hurry! Hurry!
- Let's go. Let's go.

155
00:09:20,267 --> 00:09:26,967
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

156
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:46,967
- [ANDY] Hey, Leon.
- Hey, Uncle.

157
00:09:47,133 --> 00:09:49,600
You guys have been coming
here a lot lately, huh?

158
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:50,933
- Have a seat.
- Oh, yeah.

159
00:09:51,033 --> 00:09:53,700
- I hope I'm not intruding.
- No, no. Not at all.

160
00:09:53,833 --> 00:09:55,767
Actually, you should
get used to being here.

161
00:09:55,867 --> 00:09:57,600
We're going to be
business partners, after all.

162
00:09:57,700 --> 00:10:00,100
So, what can I do for you?

163
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:02,600
- This will be quick, Uncle.
- [PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

164
00:10:03,867 --> 00:10:05,567
I don't want to take up
too much of your time.

165
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:06,967
It's just that...

166
00:10:08,567 --> 00:10:10,967
I found a picture
in my dad's things.

167
00:10:11,067 --> 00:10:14,233
My mom hasn't finished
sorting through everything yet.

168
00:10:15,367 --> 00:10:16,800
You're in it.

169
00:10:18,900 --> 00:10:22,533
I just wanted to ask
if Sandro was there too.

170
00:10:23,667 --> 00:10:30,533
[MUSIC BECOMES GRIM]

171
00:10:36,533 --> 00:10:37,733
Uhm... [SNIFFLES]

172
00:10:38,767 --> 00:10:40,500
I think, uh... [HUFFS]

173
00:10:41,233 --> 00:10:43,333
[ANDY] You know,
honestly, this--

174
00:10:43,867 --> 00:10:44,933
[SIGHS]

175
00:10:45,067 --> 00:10:47,367
T-This was taken, uh...
during one of our...

176
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:49,100
common friends' gatherings.

177
00:10:49,233 --> 00:10:50,433
It's either, uh...

178
00:10:50,567 --> 00:10:53,500
a birthday or
an anniversary, so...

179
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:56,067
I don't...

180
00:10:56,467 --> 00:10:58,567
I don't even know
everyone I'm with in this photo.

181
00:11:00,467 --> 00:11:01,600
Uhm...

182
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:05,400
Has your concern about Sandro
still not been resolved?

183
00:11:05,967 --> 00:11:07,767
Uh, kind of, uncle.

184
00:11:09,667 --> 00:11:11,700
It would help more if...

185
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,267
I knew what he looked like.

186
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,067
Well, uh...

187
00:11:17,167 --> 00:11:18,633
I wish I could help more.

188
00:11:18,767 --> 00:11:19,967
It's okay, uncle.

189
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:24,100
I believe I'll eventually
find out the truth about him.

190
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:26,200
Okay.

191
00:11:27,267 --> 00:11:28,200
[LEON] I have to go, uncle.

192
00:11:28,333 --> 00:11:30,067
Alright. Take care.

193
00:11:30,167 --> 00:11:37,267
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

194
00:11:54,700 --> 00:11:55,667
Jade.

195
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:58,433
Are they our guests
getting married next week?

196
00:11:58,533 --> 00:12:00,633
Uh, yes.

197
00:12:01,367 --> 00:12:02,900
Wait, why are you here?

198
00:12:03,033 --> 00:12:05,167
Ah, Martin said
I'd handle things for now

199
00:12:05,333 --> 00:12:06,500
in case he's busy.

200
00:12:06,633 --> 00:12:10,100
- [JADE] Ah.
- [KIKO] Oh, sir, ma'am.

201
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:12,500
I'm Kiko. I'm one of
the staff assisting you.

202
00:12:12,667 --> 00:12:16,900
If you have any welcome baskets
for your guests,

203
00:12:17,067 --> 00:12:18,033
we'll be the ones
to arrange them

204
00:12:18,167 --> 00:12:19,700
and place them in their rooms.

205
00:12:19,833 --> 00:12:21,700
[BRIDE] Hmm. Welcome baskets?

206
00:12:22,367 --> 00:12:23,767
That's such a great idea.

207
00:12:23,900 --> 00:12:25,033
Alright, we'll prepare those.

208
00:12:25,167 --> 00:12:26,767
Yes, ma'am.
Just let me know right away.

209
00:12:26,900 --> 00:12:27,967
I'll personally take care of it.

210
00:12:28,067 --> 00:12:29,000
[BRIDE] Okay, okay.

211
00:12:29,133 --> 00:12:30,167
Please have a seat.

212
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:31,767
- Have some snacks first.
- Have a seat.

213
00:12:33,733 --> 00:12:37,533
It's nice how attentive the
staff here are at Hotel 88.

214
00:12:37,667 --> 00:12:40,367
Your bosses should
give you a raise.

215
00:12:40,533 --> 00:12:43,100
[SNICKERS] Oh no, sir,
that's not necessary.

216
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:46,667
We're actually the owners,
so we always give our best.

217
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:50,633
So at your age,
you're already the owner?

218
00:12:51,033 --> 00:12:52,967
Yes. My brother and I,

219
00:12:53,100 --> 00:12:55,967
along with Jade
and her siblings.

220
00:12:56,100 --> 00:12:57,567
[BRIDE] Oh, impressive!

221
00:12:57,700 --> 00:12:59,500
Ah, Kiko, can I ask?

222
00:13:00,033 --> 00:13:02,167
Um, do you have a girlfriend?

223
00:13:03,533 --> 00:13:06,067
[SNICKERS] No.
Very single, ma'am.

224
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:09,567
[BRIDE] Hmm, no girlfriend.
Perfect.

225
00:13:09,733 --> 00:13:11,867
Love, I'll introduce him
to Rose. [CHUCKLES]

226
00:13:13,767 --> 00:13:14,733
[CHUCKLES]

227
00:13:14,900 --> 00:13:16,133
Rose?

228
00:13:16,933 --> 00:13:18,367
Who is she?

229
00:13:18,933 --> 00:13:20,200
Your coordinator?

230
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:22,233
[BRIDE] No.
My maid of honor.

231
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:23,833
She's single too.

232
00:13:23,967 --> 00:13:25,167
She and Kiko would be perfect.

233
00:13:25,300 --> 00:13:29,933
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

234
00:13:30,067 --> 00:13:32,333
So, what do you think?
Is that okay?

235
00:13:34,367 --> 00:13:36,233
Yes. No problem.

236
00:13:37,633 --> 00:13:39,733
[BRIDE] Let me get your social.

237
00:13:42,867 --> 00:13:45,433
They would look
good together, right?

238
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:47,567
- Here.
- It's nice, she's single.

239
00:13:47,700 --> 00:13:48,900
[CHUCKLING]

240
00:13:49,033 --> 00:13:55,833
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

241
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:00,233
[SIPS]

242
00:14:00,333 --> 00:14:04,100
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

243
00:14:04,233 --> 00:14:06,033
[ANDY] You can't fool me, Leon.

244
00:14:06,567 --> 00:14:08,467
<i>You didn't get that
from your father.</i>

245
00:14:10,467 --> 00:14:11,633
<i> From Sandro--</i>

246
00:14:11,767 --> 00:14:13,967
<i>That's where that picture
came from.</i>

247
00:14:17,467 --> 00:14:19,867
<i>If you don't stop
what you're doing, Leon...</i>

248
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,900
<i>you'll get dragged into
something at the wrong time.</i>

249
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:29,867
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

250
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:35,833
[SIGHS] Leon.

251
00:14:36,833 --> 00:14:39,333
Do you think Andy
is telling the truth?

252
00:14:39,767 --> 00:14:40,733
No.

253
00:14:45,333 --> 00:14:47,767
If he said he'd never seen
Sandro at all,

254
00:14:48,367 --> 00:14:50,000
I might have believed him.

255
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:52,500
But them being together
at an event?

256
00:14:53,533 --> 00:14:55,833
There's no way
he doesn't know Sandro.

257
00:14:57,533 --> 00:14:59,633
Our world here
on the island is small.

258
00:15:00,533 --> 00:15:02,833
Do you want me to follow Andy?

259
00:15:03,500 --> 00:15:05,500
Or the other people
in the picture?

260
00:15:06,333 --> 00:15:07,533
Not yet.

261
00:15:08,167 --> 00:15:09,600
What I need to know is

262
00:15:09,733 --> 00:15:11,767
whether Sandro
has any living relatives.

263
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:13,867
That's what you find out.

264
00:15:14,033 --> 00:15:14,967
Okay.

265
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:17,300
[EXHALES HEAVILY]

266
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:19,333
I'll go over everything I know.

267
00:15:22,633 --> 00:15:24,167
[LEON]<i> Maybe there's something
</i> I don't remember

268
00:15:24,300 --> 00:15:26,300
from the day I ran over Sandro.

269
00:15:27,700 --> 00:15:30,500
<i>That could help me
find the truth.</i>

270
00:15:32,167 --> 00:15:34,367
<i>I need to go back
to that place.</i>

271
00:15:47,433 --> 00:15:50,500
- [PHONE RINGING]
- "Caller Unknown"

272
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:55,300
[RINGING CONTINUES]

273
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:02,233
[RINGING CONTINUES]

274
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:04,667
"Caller Unknown"

275
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:10,867
Hello?

276
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:18,733
Hello.

277
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:21,233
[PETER]<i> It's good
</i> to hear you again.

278
00:16:21,367 --> 00:16:28,433
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

279
00:16:30,867 --> 00:16:31,933
Peter?

280
00:16:33,067 --> 00:16:34,533
<i> It's good to hear that...</i>

281
00:16:34,633 --> 00:16:36,767
<i> you haven't forgotten me.</i>

282
00:16:38,233 --> 00:16:39,433
[GASPS]

283
00:16:40,133 --> 00:16:41,200
[BREATH QUIVERS]

284
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:43,100
- [KNOCKS ON DOOR]
- [GASPS]

285
00:16:43,300 --> 00:16:44,467
Who's that?!

286
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:47,567
[STAFF] Ma'am,
you have a visitor.

287
00:16:49,433 --> 00:16:51,933
A man. He says
he's your friend.

288
00:16:52,067 --> 00:16:57,900
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

289
00:17:00,333 --> 00:17:02,100
Next time, don't let
anyone in unless we say so.

290
00:17:02,233 --> 00:17:05,267
- But ma'am, you know him.
- It doesn't matter.

291
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:11,267
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

292
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:16,433
[MUSIC BECOMES GENTLE]

293
00:17:16,633 --> 00:17:17,800
Gio?

294
00:17:17,933 --> 00:17:23,000
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

295
00:17:23,167 --> 00:17:24,767
What are you doing here?

296
00:17:24,867 --> 00:17:29,133
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

297
00:17:29,300 --> 00:17:30,733
I heard you were sick?

298
00:17:36,833 --> 00:17:37,967
Kind of?

299
00:17:38,100 --> 00:17:44,833
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

300
00:17:57,067 --> 00:17:58,633
You don't even have a fever.

301
00:18:00,233 --> 00:18:02,967
My head hurts and I have a cold.

302
00:18:05,367 --> 00:18:07,800
It's not that bad,
you should've gone to work.

303
00:18:11,667 --> 00:18:14,367
So, did you come here
just to tell me to go to work?

304
00:18:16,567 --> 00:18:18,600
Well, you like working,
don't you?

305
00:18:19,867 --> 00:18:21,967
Plus, your siblings are
over there with you anyway.

306
00:18:25,033 --> 00:18:26,533
Gio.

307
00:18:26,667 --> 00:18:27,700
What?

308
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:31,367
You got something to say?

309
00:18:35,367 --> 00:18:36,867
Thanks for coming.

310
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:40,300
As if I'm the only one
who came here.

311
00:18:42,333 --> 00:18:43,700
Yeah.

312
00:18:43,833 --> 00:18:46,633
Yeah. I haven't had
any other visitors.

313
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:51,567
Okay, I'm off.

314
00:18:52,733 --> 00:18:53,900
Don't bother having
your security escort me out.

315
00:18:54,067 --> 00:18:56,367
Just tell them to keep a
better eye on the place, okay?

316
00:18:56,567 --> 00:19:03,433
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

317
00:19:04,267 --> 00:19:05,733
Gio...

318
00:19:11,133 --> 00:19:13,567
[YAWNING]

319
00:19:13,700 --> 00:19:16,400
- [TRIXIE] Hey! Stop that!
- Mm? What's your problem?

320
00:19:16,533 --> 00:19:19,400
I'm not even doing
anything to you, okay?

321
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:23,033
Don't make it so obvious
that we stayed up all night.

322
00:19:23,133 --> 00:19:25,233
Why? We did stay up all night.

323
00:19:25,367 --> 00:19:27,267
What time did we finish
digging through--

324
00:19:27,433 --> 00:19:29,200
[SHUSHING]
You're so loud!

325
00:19:29,333 --> 00:19:31,267
You're really noisy, Cheska.

326
00:19:31,433 --> 00:19:32,733
- I can't deal with you.
- I'm loud?

327
00:19:32,833 --> 00:19:35,800
There's no one here,
no one's gonna hear us.

328
00:19:35,967 --> 00:19:38,233
You're being dramatic.
I'm sleepy.

329
00:19:38,333 --> 00:19:40,433
No one's here?
Look, there's your bro.

330
00:19:40,600 --> 00:19:42,200
I'm gonna get going now.

331
00:19:42,300 --> 00:19:45,633
Bro! Hey, bro!

332
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:47,733
Here are the flowers
you asked me to buy.

333
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:50,600
There you go.

334
00:19:50,733 --> 00:19:54,467
I bought it in town,
but I talked them down to 350.

335
00:19:54,633 --> 00:19:57,967
Actually, I won't
charge you if it's for Jade.

336
00:19:58,133 --> 00:20:01,267
Wow! Thank you.

337
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,633
Ah!

338
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:05,633
So it is confirmed,
it's for Jade, right?

339
00:20:05,767 --> 00:20:07,600
Wait, why flowers? I thought--

340
00:20:07,700 --> 00:20:09,300
Don't say another word.

341
00:20:09,467 --> 00:20:13,800
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

342
00:20:13,933 --> 00:20:15,833
I hope I can
make her smile today.

343
00:20:17,333 --> 00:20:18,467
[SQUEALS]

344
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:20,333
Look at you, flower boy!

345
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:23,967
- Anyway, thanks, Cheska.
- Sure! You're welcome.

346
00:20:24,100 --> 00:20:27,400
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

347
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:29,933
[GRUNTS SOFTLY]

348
00:20:31,200 --> 00:20:35,000
[ENGINE REVVING]

349
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:37,500
[HANDBRAKE ENGAGING]

350
00:20:37,633 --> 00:20:40,000
Looks like this is
as far as we go, sir.

351
00:20:40,167 --> 00:20:42,500
- Sari's place is further in.
- [MARTIN] You're right.

352
00:20:43,900 --> 00:20:45,667
[CAR DOORS OPEN]

353
00:20:47,667 --> 00:20:49,300
[CAR DOORS CLOSE]

354
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:56,167
[HOPEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

355
00:20:58,333 --> 00:21:00,633
Monette! Let's go!

356
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:03,533
Sir, my suggestion

357
00:21:03,700 --> 00:21:05,433
is you should've
just handled this yourself.

358
00:21:05,533 --> 00:21:07,133
You didn't have
to drag me into it!

359
00:21:07,233 --> 00:21:10,833
I need a friendly face so
Sari doesn't just kick me out!

360
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:11,867
Sir...

361
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,533
Kiko and I have
so much work to do.

362
00:21:13,667 --> 00:21:15,900
Don't we have
a wedding guest coming?

363
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:19,367
If Sari doesn't come back
as my assistant,

364
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:21,833
then you're going
to be the new assistant.

365
00:21:21,933 --> 00:21:24,467
Really?
You can't fool me, sir.

366
00:21:24,567 --> 00:21:27,167
That's the same thing
you told Raphie.

367
00:21:27,267 --> 00:21:29,067
Do I look like I'm joking?

368
00:21:32,733 --> 00:21:34,167
I'm coming, sir! Let's go!

369
00:21:34,267 --> 00:21:36,333
Let's go! Sari?!
We're coming!

370
00:21:36,433 --> 00:21:39,033
Sari, we're on our way!

371
00:21:43,567 --> 00:21:44,433
[MARTIN CLEARS THROAT]

372
00:21:47,267 --> 00:21:48,367
Sari?

373
00:21:49,133 --> 00:21:51,433
- [MONETTE] Sari?
- Sari?

374
00:21:51,567 --> 00:21:52,667
[MONETTE] Sari?

375
00:21:53,267 --> 00:21:55,233
[MONETTE] Come on,
go back to the hotel.

376
00:21:58,067 --> 00:21:59,067
[MONETTE] Sari?

377
00:21:59,233 --> 00:22:01,333
What priest?
There is no priest here!

378
00:22:03,933 --> 00:22:06,200
Go to the church,
there is a priest there.

379
00:22:07,633 --> 00:22:09,033
- [BOTONG] Hmm?
- Grandpa, it's "Sari."

380
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:10,933
I am the one
they are looking for.

381
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:13,167
Then why don't you face them?

382
00:22:13,267 --> 00:22:16,200
That is Sir Martin, Grandpa.
I don't want to talk to him.

383
00:22:16,933 --> 00:22:20,933
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

384
00:22:21,100 --> 00:22:23,033
Dear, we are not rude.

385
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:24,367
- You need to face...
- I do not want to.

386
00:22:24,467 --> 00:22:26,400
the people who come here
properly.

387
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:27,600
- Grandpa.
- Oh?

388
00:22:27,767 --> 00:22:28,633
- Grandpa-- Grandpa!
- Hey!

389
00:22:28,767 --> 00:22:30,233
Uh, good day to you!

390
00:22:30,900 --> 00:22:31,867
- Oh!
- Oh.

391
00:22:31,967 --> 00:22:33,267
Come closer. Come closer.

392
00:22:34,067 --> 00:22:35,100
Hello.

393
00:22:35,267 --> 00:22:36,400
- [BOTONG] Hmm.
- Good day, Grandpa.

394
00:22:36,567 --> 00:22:38,200
- Good day.
- Ah, we are, uh...

395
00:22:38,300 --> 00:22:40,233
we are Sari's colleagues
from the hotel.

396
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:42,567
- [BOTONG] Ah.
- Is she here?

397
00:22:42,667 --> 00:22:44,100
Ah...

398
00:22:45,333 --> 00:22:52,400
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

399
00:22:57,533 --> 00:22:58,600
Sir.

400
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:00,767
You are dead.

401
00:23:01,333 --> 00:23:03,100
Looks like you have
been marked.

402
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:10,267
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

403
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:16,933
[FAUCET CREAKS]

404
00:23:17,033 --> 00:23:18,400
[WATER RUNNING]

405
00:23:19,833 --> 00:23:21,600
<i> All of them are at Hotel 88.</i>

406
00:23:21,700 --> 00:23:22,633
<i> I saw something.</i>

407
00:23:22,833 --> 00:23:24,767
<i>- Hello, Philippines!
- And hello, world!</i>

408
00:23:24,867 --> 00:23:26,667
<i>- Welcome to Hotel 88.
- Welcome to Hotel 88.</i>

409
00:23:26,833 --> 00:23:28,367
<i>- The once-closed hotel
- The once-closed hotel</i>

410
00:23:28,500 --> 00:23:30,333
<i>- but is now back!
- but is now back!</i>

411
00:23:30,833 --> 00:23:31,967
<i> Solenn...</i>

412
00:23:32,067 --> 00:23:33,300
<i> Luna...</i>

413
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:36,700
<i>Whatever they call you,
I'm calling you mine.</i>

414
00:23:36,833 --> 00:23:37,800
<i> Why is that?</i>

415
00:23:37,967 --> 00:23:39,200
<i> The past always finds a way</i>

416
00:23:39,333 --> 00:23:40,933
<i>to catch up
with our lives today.</i>

417
00:23:41,033 --> 00:23:42,600
<i>You need to throw
that phone away.</i>

418
00:23:42,700 --> 00:23:44,133
<i> Your life is in danger!</i>

419
00:23:44,233 --> 00:23:45,933
<i>- He is dangerous!
- [GRUNTING]</i>

420
00:23:46,033 --> 00:23:47,133
- [SCREAMS]
<i> - Hey!</i>

421
00:23:47,233 --> 00:23:48,333
<i> Why do you even care?</i>

422
00:23:48,500 --> 00:23:49,467
<i>Do you think
I am scared of you?</i>

423
00:23:49,633 --> 00:23:50,333
[GUN COCKS]

424
00:23:50,500 --> 00:23:52,667
Maybe this will make you scared.

425
00:23:52,833 --> 00:23:53,667
<i> Peter!</i> [SOBS]

426
00:23:53,833 --> 00:23:55,800
I will not go into this venture

427
00:23:55,933 --> 00:23:57,200
<i> if he is involved.</i>

428
00:23:57,367 --> 00:23:59,500
<i>It is either me
or Andy Arellano.</i>
